    <body>
      <group id="content" extype="content">
        <trans-unit id="101" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" extradata="MT" restype="x-metadata">
          <source>Register sales commissions</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="102" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" extradata="MT" restype="x-metadata">
          <source>This procedure shows you how sales commissions are calculated and registered.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="103" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Register sales commissions</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="104" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>This procedure shows you how sales commissions are calculated and registered.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="105" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>You can run this procedure in demo data company USMF or on your own data.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="106" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Before starting this guide, run the guide called "Set up sales commission rules" to make sure that you have all the necessary commission calculation setup.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="107" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Take note of the customer and item numbers that you have chosen for the commission process and use them when asked to create a sales order in this guide.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="108" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Invoice a sales order that qualifies a salesperson for a commission</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="109" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Go to Sales and marketing &gt; Sales orders &gt; All sales orders.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="110" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Click New.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="111" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>In the Customer account field, click the drop-down button to open the lookup.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="112" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>In the list, find and select the desired record.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="113" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>In the list, click the link in the selected row.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="114" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Click OK.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="115" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>On the Action Pane, click Options.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="116" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Click Change view.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="117" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Click Header view.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="118" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Expand the Setup section.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="119" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>The value in the Sales group field represents a group with one or more sales representatives assigned to it.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="120" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>The people in the group are the ones who will receive commissions when the order is invoiced, as per predefined rates and distribution.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="121" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>The value is copied from the Customer card, but you can change it if you wish.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="122" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>The Sales group is also copied to the sales order line.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="123" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>You can change it so that it can differ from the one in the header and/or between lines.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="124" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>The value in the Commission group field represents a group that you have created for one or more customers with the purpose of tracking commissions.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="125" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>The value is copied from the Customer card, but you can change it if you wish.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="126" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>On the Action Pane, click Options.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="127" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Click Change view.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="128" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Click Line view.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="129" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>In the Item number field, click the drop-down button to open the lookup.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="130" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>In the list, select the item you have set up for commissions.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="131" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>In the Quantity field, enter a number.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="132" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Take note of the line's Net amount.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="133" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>It represents the sales revenue, which in this example is the basis for commission calculation.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="134" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Click Save.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="135" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>On the Action Pane, click Invoice.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="136" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Click Invoice.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="137" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Expand the Parameters section.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="138" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>In the Quantity field, select 'All'.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="139" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Select Yes in the Posting field.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="140" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Click OK.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="141" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Click OK.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="142" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>It may take a minute or so to post the transaction.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="143" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Allow the processing to complete and donâ€™t close the page.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="144" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Review the registered sales commissions</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="145" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>On the Action Pane, click Invoice.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="146" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Click Invoice.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="147" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>On the Action Pane, click Invoice.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="148" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Click Commission transactions.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="149" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>The Overview tab displays lines representing the commission amounts payable to sales representatives who are associated with the invoiced sales order.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="150" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Let's review the details.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="151" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>If you used the "Set up sales commission rules" guide to set up the Commission sales group, there are two sales people to receive a sales commissions, and the commission is split equally between them.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="152" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>In this example, the total amount of the commission is calculated as a percentage of the sales revenue (the net amount of order line).</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="153" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Close the page.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="154" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Click Voucher.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="155" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>You can review the voucher transactions for the commission amounts that have been posted to the predefined commission expense and commission payable accounts.</source>
        </trans-unit>
